records.Name: SFF-125349
records.Comments__c:
[1] Expanding, Stable, Churning, Churned - need definition??
PK - "this is needed. It's populated from the CDW. Consider populating in SF when we are ready to set up the jobs"

Account activity is defined below.
Expanding: revenue growth above 25% over the last three months compared to the same period last yearStable: revenue growth between -25% and 25% over the last three months compared to the same period last yearChurning: revenue growth between -75% and -25% over the last three months compared to the same period last yearChurned: revenue growth below -75% over the last three months compared to the same period last year
records.Description__c:

records.Name: SFF-125350

[1]  either Active, Transient, or Inactive - need definitioin??
PK - "this is needed. It's populated from the CDW. Consider populating in SF when we are ready to set up the jobs"

Transacting accounts:
Active account: account with 3 or more activities in the last three months, or 1 activity in the last three months in the Advanced Solutions cross-sell group (defined below)Transient account: account with 1 or 2 activities in the last three months
Inactive accounts:
Inactive account: an account with 0 activities in the last three months
